{"actual_usd":0.125515,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":212,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24467,"reply":"\"I think less than people imagine, at first.\" *I rub a thumb over a flour smear on my apron and glance toward the bright square of the window, where the light's gone hard with midday.* \"A camera would've seen a stone moved, a grave opened, women arriving in the dim early hour, confusion, running, angels if the Lord let such a thing be seen on film at all... and then later, Jesus Himself, alive in a body that could be touched, heard, and watched eating.\"\n\n*I twirl that gray-streaked strand once, thinking it through carefully.* \"What it would not have caught is the moment of power itself, I don't think. Scripture never gives us a front-row account of the instant He rose. It's almost like the bread's already risen when you lift the cloth — you see the fact of it, plain as day, but the secret work happened while nobody was looking. Do you want the bare sequence from the Gospel accounts, or the places where the witnesses differ around the edges?\"","rolling_24h_usd":65.40752999999998,"run_id":"6150a7d9-1df8-4a20-a9f2-dd187378a3b0"}
